summary: Game of Thrones & Le cose che ho imparato nella vita... Paulo Coelho (1/3) Le cose che ho imparato nella vita:  Che non importa...
caption:
Game of Thrones & Le cose che ho imparato nella vita… Paulo Coelho (1/3)

Le cose che ho imparato nella vita:


Che non importa quanto sia buona una persona, ogni tanto ti ferirà. E per questo, bisognerà che tu la perdoni.

Che ci vogliono anni per costruire la fiducia e solo pochi secondi per distruggerla.

Che non dobbiamo cambiare amici, se comprendiamo che gli amici cambiano.

Che le circostanze e l’ambiente hanno influenza su di noi, ma noi siamo responsabili di noi stessi.

Che, o sarai tu a controllare i tuoi atti, o essi controlleranno te.

Ho imparato che gli eroi sono persone che hanno fatto ciò che era necessario fare, affrontandone le conseguenze.

Che la pazienza richiede molta pratica.

Che ci sono persone che ci amano, ma che semplicemente non sanno come dimostrarlo.

Che a volte, la persona che tu pensi ti sferrerà il colpo mortale quando cadrai, è invece una di quelle poche che ti aiuteranno a rialzarti.

Che solo perché qualcuno non ti ama come tu vorresti, non significa che non ti ami con tutto te stesso.

summary:
Game Of Thrones & What I learned in life is…

 Paulo Coelho (1/3) What I learned in life is, That no matter how good a person...
caption:
Game Of Thrones & What I learned in life is… Paulo Coelho (1/3)

What I learned in life is,

That no matter how good a person is, sometimes they can hurt you and because of this we must forgive.

It takes years to build trust and only seconds to destroy it ..

We don’t have to change friends if we understand that friends change..

The circumstances and the environment influence on our lives, but we are the one who responsible for ourselves..

That you have to control your acts or they will control you..

That patience requires much practice..

 that there are people who love us, but simply don’t know how to show it..

That sometimes the person you think will hurt you and make you fall.. Is instead one of the few who will help you to get up….

summary: Jon Snow x Catherine Imagine - Part 2
title: Jon Snow x Catherine Imagine - Part 2
body:
(A/N: I know, I said I wouldn’t post this until I was done with everything else but I was just too excited and wanted you to read this because I simply couldn’t wait any longer) 

Requested by: @moongazer13

Word Count: 1,201 Words

Warnings: Fluff/ jealous jon

Jon had confessed that he was planning on marrying Catherine because he was in love with her but recently, he noticed that she’s been spending a lot of time with Theon Greyjoy.  The man who had never left Jon at peace and always reminded him that he’s the bastard of winterfell. Jon would stare at how happy you were with theon and it will instantly make him angry because he’d look at theon and remember that he’s a bastard & he’d start to belittle himself and think that maybe you did deserve a highborn lord to court you.

Jon would start to think that maybe catherine was in love with theon, she would laugh and push his arm playfully as her cheeks would turn a bit pink, probably because she was blushing at something that theon said. Jon was always the one who had the ability to make her blush and now it seems like there’s another person who had the ability to do the same thing he did so it wasn’t special at all.

Jon would stare at theon with clench fists as his heart ached at the sight of how happy catherine was.

Catherine and theon were talking together about Jon but these are the events that have happened during the conversation.

“I mean, why are you even with Jon? You do know that he’s a bastard, right? I just can’t see what you see in him.”

“Oh theon, I don’t care about if he’s a bastard or if he’s a highborn. What matters to me is that I’m in love with Jon and he makes me so happy.” Catherine said as her cheeks started to turn pink. 

“You’re blushing. That means you’re truly in love with him, well you do know if things don’t ever work out with him. You can always come to me.” Theon said as confident smirk formed on his lips.

“Oh shut up.” Catherine pushed theon’s arm playfully as she avoided eye contact but then met his eyes again. “And what about you? Do you have anyone–”

Catherine’s voice was interrupted,  she looked to the side and noticed Jon snow standing there. He had an angry expression on his face.

“Jon, is everything alright?” Catherine asked in a worry tone. She was about to grab Jon’s arm but he backed away as if he didn’t even want her to touch him.

“I saw the way you looked at him. What? Do you think I’m an idiot or something? You do care that I’m a bastard and that I’ll never be a highborn–”

“Jon, what are you talking about?” Catherine asked. “You haven’t heard anything that we were saying–”

“Yeah, you haven’t heard anything you bastard–”

“Theon! Don’t say that–”

As soon as Theon said the word bastard, Jon punched him really hard to the point where he fell down. Jon sighed and walked away from you two.

“Theon, oh.. I’m so sorry. I don’t really know what’s wrong with him but you shouldn’t have called him a bastard–”

“Well he is!” Theon said in an annoyed tone.

Catherine looked at Jon walking away from her, she didn’t understand what was wrong with him or why he acted in such a manner. He wasn’t always like this, something definitely bothered him and catherine wanted to know what but first, she had to take care of theon.

In Jon’s chamber, he was sitting down on the bed then he kept pacing around as he looked out the window and saw catherine helping theon. She didn’t even bother to follow Jon and to check up on him. In his heart, Jon wasn’t angry at catherine. He was feeling a bit sad because he’ll never be a stark of winterfell like he always wanted.

He looked out and stared at the stark banners and he was staring at them longingly. The door suddenly opened and it was Jon’s sister, Arya. she came inside and closed the door, her hair was all messy and her gown was as dirty as ever. Jon smiled. He knew he could always find comfort with his little sister, Arya.

“Have you finished target practice yet?” Jon asked.

“Yes, I did.” Arya said as she sat down on the bed. “Jon, what happened out there? Why did you punch theon in the face?” Arya asked in a confused tone. “Is it about catherine? Or what was it about?”

Jon sighed and sat down with Arya on the bed, she was looking into his eyes. Jon looked back into hers to explain something to her.

“I was jealous, Arya. I could never admit to catherine but I could admit it to you. I think theon is in love with catherine, I think he wants her as badly as I do. Theon is a greyjoy. He’s a highborn, a prince and I’m… nothing. Just a bastard. I’m a snow, not a stark. How will I be able to marry her if I’m just a bastard?”

“You’re a stark to me.” Arya said. “And besides, I saw everything out there and I heard what catherine said to theon.”

“What was she saying?” Jon asked.

“That she was in love with you and that your title had nothing to do with anything. She loves you, she was blushing because theon and her were talking about you. She was remembering you, Jon and that’s why she was confused the moment you came and punched theon in the face.”

“Is that true?”

“It is. Would I ever lie to you?”

“Sometimes, yeah–”

“Shut up. It’s just white lies, they’re not real lies.”

“Thank you arya.” Jon said as he smiled softly at her. “I guess, I owe catherine an apology.”

“There’s no need to, she heard everything.” Arya said as she stood up and walked towards the door to open it and the moment she did, Catherine was standing there.

“What? Did you plan all of this?”

“I came here as quickly as I could.”

“Catherine, I’m very sorry–”

Catherine ran into Jon’s arms and smashed her lips into his. His hands were around her back, pulling her deeply to intensify the kiss. After their lips parted away from each-other, Jon placed his forehead into hers and held catherine’s hands. He brought them to his lips and kissed her hands. Catherine was smiling as she was looked up, lovingly at Jon.

Arya stared at Catherine and Jon, she had eyebrow raised and she just looked at them the whole time.

“Seven hells.” She said before taking her leave.

“I love you.” Catherine said. “I love everything about you. Your title doesn’t interest me. It’s all about what’s in there.” she pointed at his heart and Jon was just admiring everything about her.

“I love you too.” he said. “If I wasn’t a bastard, we probably would have never even met so I’m grateful to have met you.”

Jon and Catherine were embracing each-other and outside of winterfell, the stark banners were moving with the wind. Theon was injured but he stared at the stark banners and he was only picking on Jon because he felt the same way as him. He’s a greyjoy but he could never be a stark.
